records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody on WRIT.
Count 1, felony bail jumping - No contest plea.  Convicted.
Count 4, PTC burglary-building or dwelling - No contest plea.  Convicted.
Count 6, PTC burglary-building or dwelling - No contest plea.  Convicted.
Count 8, PTC theft-movable property - No contest plea.  Convicted.

Count 1 - Court sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for sixty-four (64) months.  Twenty-eight (28) months initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision concurrent with all sentences defendant is presently serving.
The defendant is found eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1)   Pay restitution of $2,000.00 joint and several with Brandon Rabe paid to Kenneth Alfson, $1,000.00 joint and several with Brandon Rabe paid to Stacy Schweitzer, $1,477.80 joint and several with Brandon Rabe paid to John Kunesh and $3,968.50 joint and several with Brandon Rabe paid to Capitol Insurance for the Kunesh claim;
2)   COMPAS assessment;
3)   Maintain full-time employment or work search;
4)   AODA treatment as directed;
5)   No contact with Brandon Rabe, Karen Kratz, Brett Holtz, Chris Lewis and his place of business, Stacy Schweitzer and her residence, Kenneth Alfson and his residence, Jay Goldman and John Kunesh;
6)   Random drug screens and pays for same;
7)   Maintain absolute sobriety;
8)   Submit a DNA sample and pay surcharge;
9)   Pay costs of the action; and 
10) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.

Count 4 - Court sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for eighty-eight (88) months.  Twenty-eight (28) months initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision, concurrent with all sentences defendant is presently serving.  Conditions of extended supervision are the same except there is no restitution.

Count 6 - Court sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for eighty-eight (88) months.  Twenty-eight (28) months initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision, concurrent with all sentences defendant is presently serving.  Conditions of extended supervision are the same except there is no restitution.

Count 8 - Court sentences defendant to six (6) months Manitowoc County Jail, under the Huber law, concurrent with all sentences defendant is presently serving.

Court dismisses and reads in Counts 2, 3, 5 and 7 as well as uncharged misdemeanor theft offenses from the following Manitowoc County Sheriffs Department referrals:  14-2676, 14-1428, 14-1483, 14-1970, 14-2589, 14-2660, 14-2662, 14-2663, 14-2665 and 14-1999.

Court orders the defendant to make restitution payments from any earnings made while in prison and that restitution be paid first to citizen victims, then to co-defendant Brett Holtz and then to Capitol Insurance.
Minutes.
